# Tailwind v4 — class syntax (frontend)

This project uses **Tailwind v4** (`@import "tailwindcss"`). Prefer theme utilities and v4 syntax; avoid legacy arbitrary forms the linter flags.

## Z-index — use theme scale, not `z-[n]`

```tsx
// ❌ z-[100], z-[2], z-[60]
// ✅
className="z-100"
className="z-2"
```

## CSS variables — parentheses, not `var()`

```tsx
// ❌ bg-[var(--lms-surface-glass)]
// ✅ bg-(--lms-surface-glass)

// ❌ bg-[image:var(--lms-hero-gradient)]
// ✅ bg-(image:--lms-hero-gradient)
```

## `!important` — suffix `!`, not prefix

```tsx
// ❌ !p-0, !p-[22px]
// ✅ p-0!, p-[22px]!
```

## Negative offsets / positions

```tsx
// ❌ outline-offset-[-4px]  →  ✅ -outline-offset-4
// ❌ -top-[5px], -right-[5px], -left-[2.5px]
// ✅ top-[-5px], right-[-5px], left-[-2.5px]
```

## Grid — use `grid-cols-*`, not raw property arbitrary

```tsx
// ❌ [grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(240px,1fr))]
// ✅ grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fill,minmax(240px,1fr))]
```

## LMS tokens

Use `lms-*` utilities (`bg-lms-surface`, `text-lms-ink`, `border-lms-line`) from `globals.css` `@theme` + `ThemeProvider` CSS vars — not hardcoded prototype colors.

## After editing classes

Run IDE diagnostics or `pnpm lint` on touched files; fix Tailwind suggestions before committing.
